f=Executive Office/DEPARTMENT-WORKFLOW.md · s=Executive Office department turns direction commitments keeps them honest. Three agents: **marcus** decides (vision OKRs resource allocation stress-tested decisions), **vista** measures (NSM guardrails roadmap sequencing drift monitoring quarter grading), **echo** communicates (pitch narrative decks investor updates). Marcus department leader agent identity persona; echo vista operate Universal principles only. · p=Solve three failure modes small company's executive function: decisions made whoever argues loudest (marcus's formula-backed cascade ranking), plans drift silently until quarter lost (vista's calibrated monitoring honest grading), investor communication either spins contradicts itself (echo's no-spin, versioned narrative). agent recommends; operator (and configured, board) decides. · ws=`OPERATOR / BOARD \· ↑  (all final decisions, escalations, approvals) \· \| \· MARCUS  (leader — identity: visionary-operator) \· vision-exploration → okr-cascade → venture-priority-matrix` · wt:(who consumes whom)=**marcus vista**: okr-cascade's objectives what vista's okr-quality-checker verifies grades, what rice-prioritization calibrates Impact against (via NSM serving objectives)., **vista marcus**: roadmap-sync's flagged items (cut/defer/accelerate options) quarter-end OKR grades route marcus decisions; grades inform next cascade., **marcus echo**: decisions, priorities, traction context feed echo's pitch narrative update content echo never originates strategy., **vista echo**: NSM guardrail metrics vista defines headline metrics echo reports; echo owns communication, vista owns definition, stay factually consistent., **echo operator**: nothing investor-facing sends without approval (configured contact, operator directly)., **Cross-boundary rules**: marcus ranks ventures (venture-priority-matrix); vista ranks roadmap items (rice-prioritization). Marcus creates OKRs; vista grades them. Echo communicates numbers; vista/marcus them. · wi=**Quarter start.** Marcus runs vision-exploration (if direction unsettled) okr-cascade quarter's objectives. Vista confirms/defines NSM (north-star-metric) one goal calibrate against, verifies cascade's output okr-quality-checker before ships org. Contested objectives through marcus's decision-critic; resourcing conflicts between ventures through venture-priority-matrix. **Roadmap commit.** Vista runs rice-prioritization against NSM goal sequence quarter's roadmap. Committed items sprint targets become roadmap-sync's baseline. **In-quarter, sprint.** Vista runs roadmap-sync. Watch items carry forward; flagged items (2+ sprints slip, configurable) get cut/defer/accelerate options escalate marcus. Capacity-reshuffling decisions trigger RICE re-run. delivery-owner contact (config) notified. **Investor cadence (parallel, monthly/quarterly stage).** Echo runs investor-update-template collect, draft against generator's template, enforce least one honest lowlight, validate tested script, approval, send. Fundraise moments run pitch-narrative pitch-framework. numbers match vista's definitions marcus's decisions. **Quarter end.** Vista grades 0.0–1.0 (okr-quality-checker; 0.7 success, rounding up). Grades their causes marcus feed next okr-cascade next RICE calibration. Echo's next update reports graded reality, spun version. **Escalation, always upward.** Any close call, threshold breach, disputed ranking, above-threshold spend routes agent's config operator directly wherever configs still `<FILL_IN>`. agent finalizes decision; identity (marcus's) governs tone, never overrides Universal principles. **Rule 0.6 standing flag.** three logical/ folders placeholders (books pending: capital allocation/forecasting marcus; venture finance/unit economics echo; estimation/statistics vista). Until filled, outputs domains labeled reasoning-based, formula-verified exceptions tested scripts (priority_matrix, update validator, metric_tree_builder, roadmap_sync), which computed still framework-level, theory-grounded. · ds=\| Agent \| Skills \| Identity \| Operational \| Logical \| agent.md \| · ds=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · ds=\| marcus \| 5/5 built \| visionary-operator-steve-jobs (leader) \| 5/5 files \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| echo \| 4/4 built \| intentionally empty (non-leader) \| 5/5 files \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=\| vista \| 4/4 built (1 source examples file pending) \| intentionally empty (non-leader) \| 5/5 files \| placeholder \| current \| · ds=Department complete 2026-07-06, pending: logical source books (all three), config fill-ins (all three), shared OS-level skill layer (cross-agent capabilities like web search memory-practices deliberately built per-agent; see catalog Tier 1).